HEADWORD: Foreside
<hw>Fore"side</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
front side; the front; esp., a stretch of country fronting the
sea.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The outside or external covering.</def>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foresight</ent>⟦br⟧
